  THE MODERATOR:   All right, looks like we'll get started here.  Thank you for being inside the virtual media center here at ANA Inspiration.  I'm pleased to be joined by Jin Young Ko.
 Without further ado, Jin Young, thank you for joining us today.  How are you doing?
 JIN YOUNG KO:   I'm doing good.
 Q. That's good.
 JIN YOUNG KO:   Yes.
 Q. Let's take it back to 2020 when you weren't able to defend here and now we're back here all over again.  Was it disappointing to you not to be able to defend your championship last year?
 JIN YOUNG KO:   Yes.  I couldn't play last year at this course because COVID, and -- but it was sad because I missed defend champion, but I'm happy to be back here in 2021, so I'm looking next four days.
 Q. Were you able to watch to last year from Korea?
 JIN YOUNG KO:   Yes, I did.
 Q. Nice.  So you were a fan?
 JIN YOUNG KO:   Yes.
 Q. Very different.  Very different.  But since rejoining the tour, especially in 2021 specifically, you've already had two Top 5 finishes.  What have you been working on in your game to get to where you are?
 JIN YOUNG KO:   Well, yeah, I had just three events this year and I finished two Top 5 and one missed the cut.
 But it was -- it was -- missed the cut was like fine because my body condition was so bad so I couldn't hit well and I didn't play well in Florida.
 But I finished good last week and first week in the Florida as well, so I'm looking forward this week.  Well, I practiced a lot in Korea with the snows.  (Laughter.)  And I know how to play in wintertime.
 Well, it was hard, but, yeah, I had a lot of practice in short game and putting and then swing, so I'm happy.
 Q. When you say you weren't happy with your body condition were you in Florida adjusting anything in your swing or were you kind of just adjusting to the tour again?
 JIN YOUNG KO:   Well, I was tired so my swing were not good, so that's make sense.  (Laughter.)
 Q. Last week you said you had a really good finish.  What do you think is the strongest part of your game right now?
 JIN YOUNG KO:   Well, I change the driver last week after first round.  I went to the Titleist center and I tried a lot of -- couple drivers and I picked really good one, so I used that one next three days and I hit really good last week.
 I had good practice last three days in Mission Hills, so I can't wait to tomorrow and next four days.
 Q. Yeah.  So we're back here at Mission Hills.  What are the memories like when you're back here coming back as a past champion?
 JIN YOUNG KO:   Of course Poppy's Pond, yeah, in 2019 I jumped in it and I want to jump in again someday.
 Q. What are some of the -- have you been on the course yet and what are some of the things that you like best about the course right now?
 JIN YOUNG KO:   Well, everything.  It's like fairway is really perfectly clearing and best --  greens are one of the best, putting green, and, well, even weather is too little hot, but it's good.
 Q. A little hot is better than snow, isn't it?
