 Q. What is it about the golf course that fits your game best?
 JIN YOUNG KO:   Well, I think I have to try -- well, fairway is narrow still and rough is thicker, but not as much in 2019.  But greens firmer than 2019, so I have to keep the fairway a lot I think for this week.
 So, well, I think I don't have to lose the focus.  Yeah.
 Q. So back here there is no grandstand.  The last time you were here there were a bunch of fans.  Is it weird for you to be back here with no fans?
 JIN YOUNG KO:   Of course, and especially I want to be like high five when I walk to the 18 greens before the bridge, but we couldn't, we can't do that in 2021.
 So it's sad, because that part is one of the good memorable in ANA Inspiration, but we can't.  It's sad.  I will do just by myself.  (Applause)  Yay!  High five.
 Q. And of course we don't have the grandstand on 18.  It's an island green.  What are your thoughts of the way it's playing?
